# Security Guidelines

## Data Protection

### User Data
- Encrypt all personal information
- Use secure storage for API keys
- Implement data retention policies
- Regular security audits

### Audio Data
- Encrypt voice recordings
- Implement secure streaming
- Auto-delete after processing
- Access control implementation

### Macro Storage
- Encrypt macro definitions
- Secure preset storage
- Access logging
- Version control for changes

## API Security

### Authentication
- Implement OAuth 2.0
- Use secure token storage
- Regular token rotation
- Rate limiting implementation

### Communication
- Use WSS for WebSocket
- HTTPS for REST APIs
- Certificate validation
- Secure headers implementation

## Application Security

### Input Validation
- Sanitize all user inputs
- Validate file uploads
- Check macro scripts
- Prevent injection attacks

### Process Isolation
- Sandbox macro execution
- Isolate voice processing
- Secure IPC implementation
- Resource access control

## Monitoring

### Audit Logging
- Log security events
- Monitor access patterns
- Track system changes
- Alert on suspicious activity

### Incident Response
- Define security protocols
- Implement auto-blocking
- Create recovery procedures
- Regular security updates
